---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="IT Consulting Chihuahua — Operations Assessment & Technology Roadmap | Facware"
  description="Stop guessing which part of your stack is holding revenue back. Facware audits your systems, maps your bottlenecks, and gives you a prioritized technology roadmap with projected ROI for each fix — before you spend a dollar on development."
  canonicalURL="https://facware.com/services/it-consulting.html"
  ogDescription="IT consulting and operations assessment for mid-market businesses in Chihuahua and the US Southwest. Prioritized roadmap, projected ROI. Free initial assessment."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Service",
      "name": "IT Consulting & Operations Assessment",
      "description": "We audit technology stacks for mid-market businesses in Mexico and the US Southwest, map operational bottlenecks, and deliver a prioritized technology roadmap with projected ROI for each initiative.",
      "provider": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Facware",
        "url": "https://facware.com"
      },
      "areaServed": ["Chihuahua, Mexico", "US Southwest"],
      "serviceType": "IT Consulting",
      "url": "https://facware.com/services/it-consulting.html",
      "offers": {
        "@type": "Offer",
        "price": "0",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Free initial 30-minute operations assessment"
      }
    }
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- PAGE HERO -->
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:10px"></i>
        <a href="/#facware_services">Services</a>
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:10px"></i>
        <span aria-current="page">IT Consulting</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>IT Consulting for Mid-Market Operations in Mexico &amp; the US Southwest</h1>
      <p>Before you invest in development, integration, or automation — you need to know which problem is actually costing you the most. We audit your systems, map your bottlenecks, and give you a prioritized roadmap with projected ROI for each fix.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PROBLEM -->
  <section class="section" id="problem" aria-labelledby="problem-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Spending Without a Strategy</p>
        <h2 id="problem-heading">Technology decisions made without a full picture cost more than doing nothing</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Most mid-market operations have accumulated technology debt — systems that were right for a previous stage of growth and are now holding the business back. The problem is, it's hard to see from inside.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-3">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Fixing symptoms, not causes</h3>
          <p class="card-text">You buy a new SaaS tool to fix a reporting problem, but the root cause is that your ERP and CRM aren't syncing. The new tool adds another manual export step. Six months later, you have one more system and the same problem.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Development spending with no ROI framework</h3>
          <p class="card-text">You've spent on development without a clear mechanism to measure whether it worked. The project delivered code — but did it save time? Did it reduce errors? Did it change a business metric? Usually nobody knows.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">No clarity on what to prioritize</h3>
          <p class="card-text">There are five things that need fixing and you can only afford to tackle two this quarter. Which two? Without a structured audit, the decision gets made on whoever argues loudest — not on which fix has the highest return.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DELIVERABLES -->
  <section class="section section--gray" id="deliverables" aria-labelledby="deliverables-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">What You Get</p>
        <h2 id="deliverables-heading">A clear picture of your stack — with a prioritized plan to improve it</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Our IT consulting engagements are structured around a specific deliverable: a prioritized technology roadmap with business-case justification for each initiative.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-2">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Current-state systems audit</h3>
          <p class="card-text">We document every system in your stack, how they're connected (or not), what manual workarounds exist, and where data integrity breaks down. You get a full map of your current technology environment — probably for the first time.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Bottleneck analysis with cost quantification</h3>
          <p class="card-text">We interview your team, trace your key operational processes, and put a dollar figure on each bottleneck. Every identified problem comes with an estimated annual labor cost — so prioritization becomes a financial decision, not a gut call.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Prioritized technology roadmap</h3>
          <p class="card-text">We deliver a ranked list of technology investments — integrations, automation opportunities, custom builds — with projected ROI, estimated investment, and implementation sequence. You can action this roadmap with any vendor, including us.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Build vs. buy vs. integrate analysis</h3>
          <p class="card-text">For each initiative, we evaluate whether the right answer is building custom software, buying a SaaS tool, integrating existing systems, or some combination. You get an honest recommendation — not one that defaults to the highest-revenue option for us.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROCESS -->
  <section class="section" id="process" aria-labelledby="process-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">How It Works</p>
        <h2 id="process-heading">From initial conversation to actionable roadmap</h2>
      </header>
      <ol class="steps-grid" role="list">
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">30-Minute Operations Assessment <span class="badge-free">(Free)</span></h3>
            <p>We start with a focused conversation about your current stack, your biggest operational pain points, and your growth context. You leave with a clear sense of whether a formal audit would be valuable — even if we never work together.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Structured Systems Audit</h3>
            <p>We conduct structured interviews with your team leads, observe key workflows, document your system architecture, and map your data flows. This typically takes 2–4 weeks depending on your organization's complexity.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Roadmap Presentation & Handoff</h3>
            <p>We present the full audit findings and technology roadmap in a working session with your leadership team. You receive all documentation and the full roadmap regardless of whether you engage us for implementation.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROOF METRICS -->
  <section class="section section--gray" aria-label="IT consulting outcomes">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="results-grid">
        <div class="results-content">
          <p class="section-eyebrow">What clients do with the roadmap</p>
          <h2>Most clients come for the audit. Most stay for the implementation.</h2>
          <ul class="results-list" role="list">
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Objective view</strong> of your stack — unbiased by vendor relationships or internal politics</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Quantified bottlenecks</strong> — every problem we identify comes with an estimated annual cost</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Actionable roadmap</strong> — ranked by ROI, not by what's technically interesting to build</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Free initial assessment</strong> — no commitment required to get a useful first conversation</span></li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/contact.html#contact-form" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:8px">Book your free assessment &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="results-image">
          <img src="/assets/images/facware/resources_facware.png" alt="IT consulting results" loading="lazy" width="600" height="450">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RELATED SERVICES -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="related-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">After the Roadmap</p>
        <h2 id="related-heading">We can execute on what we find</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-3">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/erp-integration.html" class="link-primary">ERP & System Integration</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">Integration gaps are the most common finding in our audits. We build the connections between your ERP, CRM, and operational systems — eliminating the manual reconciliation that fills the gaps.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/process-automation.html" class="link-primary">Process Automation</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">Manual workflow bottlenecks are the second most common finding. We automate the approval flows, data entry, and reporting cycles that are consuming your team's time.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/system-architecture.html" class="link-primary">System Architecture Design</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">When the audit reveals that your current architecture can't support where your business is going, we design the target-state architecture before any build begins.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA BAND -->
  <section class="cta-band" aria-labelledby="cta-band-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 id="cta-band-heading">Start with a free 30-minute conversation</h2>
      <p>No pitch deck. No commitment. Just an honest assessment of what's holding your operations back — and what it would take to fix it.</p>
      <a href="/contact.html#contact-form" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Book your free assessment &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .cta-band {
    background: var(--primary);
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: clamp(56px, 8vw, 80px) 24px;
  }
  .cta-band h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .cta-band p {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 32px;
    opacity: 0.9;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
  .btn-lg {
    padding: 14px 36px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
</style>
